   L2, Distance from center of web to center of bolts on side 1      =     203.5 mm
   L1, Distance from end of plate to center of bolts on side 1       =     557.0 mm
   J = fp*B*L1/2.0                                                   =    487.55 kN
   Bearing length, A = J - (J^2-4*(fp*B/6)*(P*L2+M))^0.5/(fp*B/3)    =     207.7 mm
   L3                                                                =     407.0 mm
   MinLd = MIN(0,P/2+M/L3)                                           =     -6.07 kN/mm
   MaxLd = MAX(0,P/2-M/L3)                                           =      8.58 kN/mm
   A < L1
   Tension per bolt, Ten=(fp*A*B/2-P)/Nrow/2                         =     29.53 kN
   a, distance from flange to edge of plate                          =     156.8 mm
   A >= a, therefore M=fp*(a^2/2-a^3/6/A)                            =      1.64 kN-m
   a2, distance from flange to nearest bolt + 0.025*d                =      81.8 mm
   perf, percentage of force to flange = (G/2)^3/ ((G/2)^3+(a2)^3)   =      0.19
   gwid, flange gusset width = (pltlen-d)/2                          =     146.5 mm
   Bolt head dia, HeadDia                                            =      39.6 mm
   xbar1 = distance from center of flange to farthest bolt           =       0.0 mm
   Percentage of force to flange, Perf=(G/2)^3/(xbar1^3 + (G/2)^3)   =      0.00 mm
   xbar=xbar1-headdia/2-(flgthk)/2                                   =      52.2 mm
   ybar=G/2-Headdia-(Flg gusset thick)/2                             =      24.2 mm
   M1=Perf*Ten*xbar/(MIN(HeadDia+2*xbar , B/2-(flg gusset thick)/2)) =    0.0752 kN-m
   wid = MIN(HeadDia+2*ybar , (pltlen-d)/2)                          =      88.0 mm
   M2=(1-Perf)*Ten*Ybar/Wid                                          =    0.1591 kN-m
   M3=MAX(M1,M2)                                                     =    0.1591 kN-m
   Required plate thickness=(6*M3/CF/Fy/MaxUc)^0.5                   =      11.0 mm
   Base plate bending on bolts = 6*M3/t^2                            =      2.41 kN-m
 
