 FLANGE GUSSET DESIGN
 
   For 1 bolt row, D1=Edge/2.0+(PltLen-d)/4.0                        =     110.8 mm
   D1<A so C=(1.0-D1/AA/2.0)*MaxBr*D1*B                              =    142.19 kN
   b=(pltlen-d)/2.0                                                  =     146.5 mm
   0<Gusset slope <1 so min gusset thickness=b/(Gusset Slope)/250*(Fy=       4.1 mm
   Selected gusset thickness, tg                                     =      12.0 mm
   h1 = (gusset slope)*b+(gusset height)                             =     196.5 mm
   Ang = ATAN(h1/b)                                                  =      0.93 mm
   Side gusset not used, so h2=h1-D1/2*TAN(Ang)                      =     122.2 mm
   ht=(h2^2+(b-d1/2)^2)^0.5                                          =     152.5 mm
   klr=0.75*ht/tg*3.464                                              =     33.01
   cc=(2*Pi^2*29000/Fy)^0.5                                          =    106.96
   klr < cc, therefore
   Allowable compression in gusset =
     Fyg*(1-(klr/cc)^2/2)/(5/3+3/8*klr/cc-(klr/cc)^3/8)              =       0.0 MN/m2
   Actual compression in gusset = C/tg/D1/sin(ang)^2                 =     166.4 MN/m2
   Allowable tension in gusset = 0.6*Fyg                             =     207.0 MN/m2
   TenAct=Ten*2*(1-Perf)                                             =     45.56 kN
   Actual tension in gusset = TenAct/tg/D1/SIN(Ang)^2                =      53.3 MN/m2
 
